  "function_name": "__internal_pivot_table",
  "justification": "This function implements the core pivot table computation for a single aggregation function. It is the internal workhorse called by the public pivot_table function after splitting list-valued aggregation arguments. The function validates value labels, groups data by index and column keys, applies aggregation, handles dropna and unstacking, reindexes axes when needed, sorts columns, fills NaN values, handles integer downcasting for len aggregations, optionally adds margins with row/column totals, and cleans up redundant headers. It matches all the specified behaviors described in the task."
}

